{
  "texts": [
    "Preprocessing is necessary in this case to recover the missing values, reduce the outliers, and normalize the data within a certain range.",
    "The entire amount of consumer data was 42,372 before pre-processing; however, five rows were eliminated by the Simple Imputer (SI) approach after preprocessing since all of the data in such rows were missing values.",
    "When this occurs, the SI is unsure of the value that should be ascribed.",
    "If the imputer discovers at least one actual value in the targeted record, it will impute some values rather than delete them.",
    "It is also crucial to keep in mind that the SI method operates column-wise, therefore you must transpose your data before using Flow chart of the proposed model for ETD."
  ]
}